body:
hi,

on my owncloud 5.0.4/ apache/2.2.14 (win32) mod_ssl/2.2.14 openssl/0.9.8l php/5.4.7 i have a problem with creation of files or subfolders within folders that cointains dots in the name.

for example trough the web panel:

1. in the root folder create folder "xxx.xxx"
2. after changing current directory to "xxx.xxx" try to create text file or subfolder (test.txt).
the "error when creating the file" occurs.

the same problem occurs  when syncing files with folders that contains dots. synclient (win32 v1.2.4 fails to upload files to folders with dots in a name).

logifile shows:

{"app":"search_lucene","message":"failed to extract meta information for \/laptop\/files\/xxx.xxx: could not open \"d:\\www\\intra-law\\owncloud\\data\\laptop\\files\\xxx.xxx\" (does not exist, or is not a file)","level":2,"time":1365799403}
{"app":"php","message":"touch(): unable to create file d:\\www\\intra-law\\owncloud\\data\/laptop\/files\/xxx-xxx\/test.txt because no such file or directory at d:\\www\\intra-law\\www\\owncloud\\lib\\files\\storage\\mappedlocal.php#122","level":2,"time":1365799410}
{"app":"php","message":"filemtime(): stat failed for d:\\www\\intra-law\\owncloud\\data\/laptop\/files\/xxx-xxx\/test.txt at d:\\www\\intra-law\\www\\owncloud\\lib\\files\\storage\\mappedlocal.php#113","level":2,"time":1365799410}
